    "description": "This is a dollar-neutral spread strategy in crude oil that trades the WTI Brent differential via two oil price CFDs (WTICOUSD and BCOUSD). The core signal assumes the spread exhibits short-term mean reversion around a slowly varying reference level: when the current spread is above its trailing 20-day average, the strategy positions for spread reversion by shorting WTI and buying Brent. When the spread is below the 20-day average, it buys WTI and shorts Brent. The intended opportunity is a mispricing between two crude benchmarks, with the edge coming from reversion of the spread toward its central tendency.",
